payloads_or_patterns:
A Postscript file containing format string specifiers like %s, %x, %n to write to arbitrary memory locations or execute commands. Example: `%!PS-Adobe-3.0
/bug {
  (%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s) = 
} def
bug` (This is a simplified example; actual RCE payloads are more complex and target specific memory addresses or functions to achieve arbitrary command execution).
